                     <interp inst="t18260406-303-person1629" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was in Leadenhall-street on the 8th of March, and saw the two prisoners near the prosecutor - Briggs drew the handkerchief from his pocket, and handed it to the other; it was then thrown on the ground - I secured them, and called to the prosecutor. I found a watch on Bates.</p>
               <p>BATES' Defence. I saw this young man passing a cart, and the officer came and said I had taken the handkerchief.</p>
               <p>BRIGGS' Defence. I had not had the handkerchief.</p>
